{
  "text": "Attribution tendency includes three aspects: internal and external causes, stabil-Y. Pan ity and controllability [CITATION_1] . Self-service bias is a comparison of individuals formed in the long-term process. Determined by stable attribution tendency, people with self-service bias tend to maintain self-esteem, denying that they are responsible for failure. They attribute failure to the outside factors. As a self-service deviation, subordinates prefer stable attribution [CITATION_2] . Subordinates with hostile attribution are more likely to feel the impact of abusive management.",
